<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Archivo+Black&family=Blaka+Hollow&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: "Erica One", cursive;
            background-color: rgb(144, 47, 47);
        }

        header {
            background-color: rgb(19, 3, 3);
        }

        h1 {
            font-family: 'Erica One', serif;
            color: rgb(155, 119, 83);
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgb(203, 64, 64), rgb(120, 30, 30));
           
            font-size: 85px;
            text-align: center;
            text-shadow: 3px 3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
            letter-spacing: 6px;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 0;
        }

        img.main-image {
            width: 400px;
            height: 400px;
            border: 3px solid black;
            display: block;
            margin: 30px auto;
        }

        textarea {
            color: rgb(18, 6, 6);
            font: italic 20px "Erica One", cursive;
            letter-spacing: 1.5px;
            text-align: justify;
            background-color: transparent;
            border-color: transparent;
            display: block;
            margin: 20px auto;
            width: 60%;
        }

        button {
            color: rgb(123, 25, 179);
            font-size: 18px;
            padding: 10px 30px;
            display: block;
            margin: 20px auto;
            cursor: pointer;
            border: 2px solid rgb(123, 25, 179);
            background-color: transparent;
            border-radius: 20px;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: rgb(123, 25, 179);
            color: white;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <!-- Background image at the top -->
    <div style="position: relative; container-type: inline-size;">
        <img src="https://ttarverlay.github.io/Hair.github.io/images/logo.jpeg" alt="not found" style="width: 9%; height: 100%;">
    </div>

    <header>
        <h1>Hot Comb</h1>
    </header>


    <img class="main-image" src="https://ttarverlay.github.io/Hair.github.io/images/pressingcomb.png" alt="pressing comb">

    <textarea name="description" rows="20" cols="50">
Hot Comb (Pressing Comb)

Metal comb with wooden handle in a metal, heated dome, United States, early 20th century

The Hot Comb, commonly known as the Pressing Comb, is a tool that rose to popularity in the early 20th century for its ability to temporarily straighten tightly coiled hair textures, like 4c hair! Oftentimes left directly on the stove to heat, the hot comb did come with an additional attachment called the Pressing Comb stove.

The Pressing Comb Stove added a new layer of excitement to the hair world with the newfound ability to do hair in any space and not just the kitchen. Oil was wiped through the hair beforehand to protect the strands and scalp from damage, adding a pleasant odor to the air during haircare time! The Hot Comb was more than a grooming tool; it was a physical representation of the Social pressures that the Black Community faced to conform to a white, straight-haired society. In today's society, the Hot Comb stands strong as a pillar in the African American Hair Care industry and Culture!
    </textarea>

    <button onclick="window.location.href='Welcome.html'">Next</button>

</body>
</html>